### Describe the bug

When calling the `Map*` methods (`MapGroup`, `MapGet`, `MapPost`, etc.) from a file other than Program.cs with `<IsAotCompatible>true</IsAotCompatible>`, the compiler reports IL3050 warnings even if the delegate closure's type information is known at compile time.

### Expected Behavior

No trim or AOT warnings are produced for calls to `Map*` methods outside of Program.cs.

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Create a new AOT web API with `dotnet new webapiaot`.
2. Create Program.cs:
    ```cs
    // Program.cs
    var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder();
    var app = builder.Build();
    app.MapGet("/", () => ""); // This line does not produce an AOT warning.
    app.UseNonProgramCs();
    app.Run();
    ```

3. Create ExternalHandlers.cs:
    ```cs
    // ExternalHandlers.cs
    public static class ExternalHandlerExtensions
    {
        public static IEndpointRouteBuilder UseNonProgramCs(this IEndpointRouteBuilder builder)
        {
            builder.MapGet("/", () => ""); // This line produces IL3050 erroneously.
            return builder;
        }
    }
    ```

4. Observe erroneous compiler warnings in IDE and at build.

### Exceptions (if any)

IL3050: Using member 'Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder.EndpointRouteBuilderExtensions.MapGet(IEndpointRouteBuilder, String, Delegate)' which has 'RequiresDynamicCodeAttribute' can break functionality when AOT compiling. This API may perform reflection on the supplied delegate and its parameters. These types may require generated code and aren't compatible with native AOT applications.

